race.comment: GRACIOUS DIVA (4) is close to a win at the fourth run back from a spell, the latest effort a third over 1200m at Moe. The extra journey looks a positive step and drawn ideally, so a big run is likely. VAAFEE (1) ran fifth at his latest appearance over 1600m at Cranbourne, finishing one length from the winner, the same beaten margin the start prior. Only needs to hold that form to shake the life out of this. JAYZEAL (2) has been given a 42-day freshen-up since finishing third at Kerang. Will strip fitter for a recent trial win just has that awkward gate to contend with. I'M DYNAMITE (7) hasn't won since June 2024 but was tested in BM66 grade last start and ran his best race for some time. A repeat of that would have him in the mix. GOLD GOVERNOR (3) was nosed out last start, which followed a good second-up run, and looms as a threat from the low draw now he's at peak fitness.
